title: Republicans warn Obama not to veto defense policy bill
text: Photo: Andrew Harnik, AP House Speaker John Boehner, R-Ohio, accompanied by Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., left, and other congressmen, signs the National Defense Authorization Act. WASHINGTON (AP) — House and Senate Republicans sent President Barack Obama a $612 billion defense policy bill on Tuesday, warning him not to veto it as part of a partisan fight over government spending.
